The task requires extracting three specific line items and their values:

1. Cash held by an entity available for day-to-day operations:
   - This can be represented by "Cash on Hand" (and possibly "Bank Deposits").
   - Based on example and order, "Cash on Hand" is the first direct cash item.

2. Tangible items held for use - fixed or tangible assets:
   - This corresponds to "Fixed Assets".

3. Amounts of tax accrued but not yet paid:
   - This corresponds to "Taxes Payable".

We must maintain original line item order as per input statement.

Looking at the input:

| Account            | Initial_amount | Initial_date | End_amount  | End_date  |
|--------------------|----------------|--------------|-------------|-----------|
| Cash on Hand       | 3000000.00     | 2023-12-31   | 2602624.45  | 2024-02-05|
| Bank Deposits      | 5000000.00     | 2023-12-31   | 4283110.81  | 2024-02-05|
| ...                | ...            | ...          | ...         | ...       |
| Fixed Assets       | 5000000.00     | 2023-12-31   | 5085889.19  | 2024-02-05|
| ...                | ...            | ...          | ...         | ...       |
| Taxes Payable      | 0.00           | 2023-12-31   | 131850.51   | 2024-02-05|

Based on example and instructions, only choose one cash item: "Cash on Hand" (first of the line items related to cash).

Extract:

- initial value1: Cash on Hand Initial_amount = 3000000.00
- end valu1: Cash on Hand End_amount = 2602624.45

- initial value2: Fixed Assets Initial_amount = 5000000.00
- end valu2: Fixed Assets End_amount = 5085889.19

- initial value3: Taxes Payable Initial_amount = 0.00
- end valu3: Taxes Payable End_amount = 131850.51
